<code>align-let.el</code> is a spot of code for aligning values in a Lisp <code>let</code> form (or similar), eg.

    (let ((x 1)
          (foo   2)
          (zz (blah)))
      ...)

becomes

    (let ((x   1)
          (foo 2)
          (zz  (blah)))
      ...)

Get the code from

: http://user42.tuxfamily.org/align-let/index.html

